} only accounted for 54{\%} of the variability in A{\textless}inf{\textgreater}d{\textless}/inf{\textgreater}. Accordingly, the correlation to performance time was significantly lower using power normalized to A{\textless}inf{\textgreater}P{\textless}/inf{\textgreater} (r = -0.75) or Est A{\textless}inf{\textgreater}P{\textless}/inf{\textgreater} (r = -0.71). In conclusion, unless normalized to A{\textless}inf{\textgreater}d{\textless}/inf{\textgreater}, level time trial performance in the field was not highly correlated to common laboratory measures. Furthermore, our field-measured A{\textless}inf{\textgreater}d{\textless}/inf{\textgreater} is easy to determine and was the single best predictor of level time trial performance.},
