r, but only by$\backslash$nsimilar to 2-7{\%}.$\backslash$nConclusions$\backslash$nDuring Push-off, FDHL MTU dynamics do not substantially confound the$\backslash$ninference of net plantarflexor MTU power from inverse dynamics ankle$\backslash$npower. However, other methodological limitations may cause inverse$\backslash$ndynamics to overestimate net MTU power; for instance, due to rigid-body$\backslash$nfoot assumptions. Moving forward, the EMG-driven modeling approach$\backslash$npresented could be applied to understand other tasks or larger$\backslash$nmultiarticular MTUs.},
